  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    MobileContextNamePatterns  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ClassDeclarationReader
    Reads annotations which mark classes.
  • Annotation Types Summary 
    Annotation Type Description
    DefaultContextIndex
    This annotation is for UI specifications when it is possible the interaction with more than one mobile context at the same time.
    DefaultPageIndex
    This annotation is for UI specifications when it is possible the interaction with more than one browser window at the same time.
    ExpectedAndroidActivities
    Is used when mobile screen needs to be identified by Android activity.
    ExpectedAndroidActivity
    Is used when mobile screen needs to be identified by Android activity.
    ExpectedContext
    This annotation is for UI specifications when it is possible the interaction with more than one mobile context at the same time.
    ExpectedPageTitle
    This annotation is for UI specifications when it is possible the interaction with more than one browser window/loaded pages at the same time.
    ExpectedURL
    This annotation is for UI specifications when it is possible the interaction with more than one browser window/loaded pages at the same time.
    ExpectedURLs  
    Frame
    This annotation is for UI specification when described UI is always inside some frame (browser clients and hybrid mobile apps).
    Frames
    Is used when it is necessary to switch from frame to frame Is useful to browser and hybrid applications.
    TimeOut
    This annotation is useful when default timeout of waiting for browser window with loaded page or mobile context by the given condition is not suitable for some UI (for example, it needs more time) It this kind of situations customized time could be specified like this @TimeOut(timeOut = 15) public class ...
